By Joyce Remi- Babayeju The novel COVID-19 pandemic in Nigeria has taken a new twist as the country records 260 fresh confirmed cases of the virus in 19 states, with Abia State leading with 67, Kano and Sokoto states recording just two cases each. The latest 260 new confirmed cases were posted on the COVID-19 situation report for 7TH June, 2020 published by the NCDC. The new cases are reported from 19 states of the country namely Abia(67), FCT(40), Lagos(38), Ogun(19), Gombe(16), Edo(14), Imo(9), Kwara(8), Katsina(8), Nasarawa(8), Borno(8), Kaduna(6), Bauchi(5), Ekiti(4), Niger(2), Ondo(2), Plateau(2), Kano(2),Sokoto(2). The good news is that there are no new case has been reported in the last 24 hours, NCDC reports. So far Nigeria has had 12486 confirmed cases 3959 cases have been discharged and 354 deaths have been recorded in 35 states including the Federal Capital Territory, FCT. Suddenly Abia State surfaced with 67 new cases just as Governor Okezie Ikpeazu tested positive to the coronavirus making the state the highest with new cases, while Lagos State seems to have respite from the virus with no new case. In a recent findings carried out by SundiataPost, most Nigerians still do not believe that COVID-19 is present here in the country as most of them claim they have not seen any patient suffering from the virus, while others dismiss it as a political scam by government officials. According to NCDC website, Coronaviruses are zoonotic, meaning they are normally transmitted between animals and people. The coronavirus disease (COVID-19) is caused by a new strain of coronavirus (SARS-CoV-2) that has not been previously identified in humans. It was first reported to WHO on the 31st of December, 2019 in Wuhan, China. Since the World Health Organisation, WHO, declared the coronavirus a pandemic, the world has recorded 7,136,765 cases, 407,068 deaths while 3,481,822 recovered. By Joyce Remi-Babayeju As the COViD-19 pandemic takes a geographical spread in the country, La